snippet.textDisplay:
I definitely believe this is the regeneration right after the "Harold Saxon" one since Missy did say two interesting things during her time. ONE, she said that the doctor was female in a previous incarnation, and TWO she doesn't remember how many regenerations she's had since she was "saxon". Meaning, Missy might have actually been a future regeneration than the current one we see. Like a River Song scenario, unless of course.... This is post Missy and he returned to his evil ways, OR this is the master being deceptive but towards these new enemies that even the SONIC can't scan instead of the doctor.
Agent C did say to trust no one, AND that he believed someone to be a double maybe even a triple agent, so with the whole spy theme it wouldn't really be that surprising if the Master was actually pretending to be evil this time to gain information on this new threat to help the doctor in his own twisted ways.

snippet.textDisplay:
Got my own theory on how this new master fits into the canon. Sounds crazy but hear me out:

My theory is it's John Simms master in disguise...

Remember tissue compression? John Simms master used it to take over this body, and infiltrate MI6.

My evidence? His Maniacal laughter is just like Simm, there's no room for him to fit in after missy as that was his final regeneration. And the biggest clue is in the preview for Episode 2 he does the 4 beats on the Morse code, which is what John Simms master had inside his head. Missy never had this as it stopped after the episode End of time.

Like I say, crazy theory. But if Simm is revealed in part 2 or even later in the series I can say "called it!"

Not gonna edit this so you can't accuse me of cheating.

snippet.textDisplay:
I’m open to see more but I’m honestly not feeling it. I’m getting a bit too many BBC Moriarty vibes and the giddiness is a little much for me. There’s something about both his performance and Jodie’s that feel more like homages (putting it kindly) to past versions of the characters than fresh adaptations.
13 may as well be 11 with a new coat of paint and this Master has the same nervous energy from Simm’s, which is a little weird because even if we’re to believe this could be a life before Missy, Simm’s Master was cured of his insanity by the end of his life.
With the creatures being from another universe we might find out the same about Sacha’a Master, but I digress, a lot.

snippet.textDisplay:
Way too many people severely overthinking this. I'm sure it'll be explained on Sunday.
Either way, I most definitely look forward to the exciting conclusion! I didn't expect to see The Master return so soon but I'm definitely not disappointed.
Only comment I've seen make the most sense is that Missy could've easily cheated death. Simply because The Master is known for doing that on numerous occasions.
There were so many times so many fans thought The Master was finally dead & gone. Just to be surprised when The Master keeps finding a way to survive.
Sure Missy might've turned over a new leaf at the end, but if the Doctor's personality can drastically change with each regeneration, why can't The Master's? If this incarnation came after Missy, it would make perfect sense. The Master had been a homicidal lunatic for so long that I didn't see him/her turning good indefinitely that easily. THAT would be lazy writing.
